## Pikaverse Architecture Note

### Core principle

Pikaverse is a **creator-first, schema-driven treasure hunt platform**. The admin pipeline is the source of truth for node structure, while the player engine is a renderer and executor of that schema. [strapi](https://strapi.io/blog/what-is-single-source-of-truth)

### Authority model

- **AdminDashboard / NodeEditor** define and edit node shape.
- **CreatorIntegration** normalizes, validates, saves, and loads hunts.
- **publish.js** exports a portable hunt snapshot.
- **player/game.js** consumes the published schema and renders it safely. [cgi](https://www.cgi.com/sites/default/files/2021-12/canonical-data-model-whitepaper-2021-en.pdf)

### Canonical node schema

The expected canonical node shape is:

- `id`
- `type`
- `title`
- `body`
- `nextNodeId`
- `ui.backgroundImage`
- `ui.textColor`
- `ui.accentColor`
- `ui.fontFamily`
- `puzzle.prompt`
- `puzzle.answers`
- `portalTargets`
- `timerSeconds` [docs.confluent](https://docs.confluent.io/platform/current/schema-registry/fundamentals/schema-evolution.html)

### Stability rules

- The engine must accept legacy hunts safely.
- New fields must be backward compatible.
- Optional fields should have safe defaults.
- Invalid or incomplete data should be normalized, warned about, or safely ignored rather than crashing the runtime. [dataexpert](https://www.dataexpert.io/blog/backward-compatibility-schema-evolution-guide)

### Rendering rule

`player/game.js` must not invent schema. It should render by node type and remain additive:
- `story` or default nodes show narrative and a continue action.
- `puzzle` nodes show prompt, input, and answer validation.
- `portal` nodes show destination buttons.
- `timer` nodes show a countdown and advance when complete. [branchboston](https://branchboston.com/schema-evolution-strategies-handling-data-structure-changes-without-breaking-pipelines/)

### Change policy

- Schema changes happen in the creator pipeline first.
- The player engine should be updated only after the admin can safely write the new shape.
- Breaking changes require explicit versioning or migration, not silent drift. [oreilly](https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/feature-flag-best/9781492050452/ch06.html)

### Working rule for new features

New features must be:
- additive,
- isolated,
- type-based,
- backward compatible,
- and non-blocking to existing rendering. [planetscale](https://planetscale.com/blog/backward-compatible-databases-changes)

## Operational flow

1. Creator edits a node in Admin.
2. CreatorIntegration normalizes the hunt.
3. publish.js exports the hunt snapshot.
4. Player loads the snapshot.
5. game.js renders according to node type without redefining structure. [perplexity](https://www.perplexity.ai/search/5f24bd85-a888-41f6-83c8-b0a8dffdedc9)

## Decision rule

If a feature changes what a node **is**, it belongs in the admin pipeline first.  
If a feature changes only how a node is **displayed or executed**, it can be added to the player second. [dataexpert](https://www.dataexpert.io/blog/backward-compatibility-schema-evolution-guide)

## Project posture

Pikaverse is currently in a **stable creator-first phase**. The goal is to preserve runtime stability while expanding node types and creator tools in a controlled, backward-compatible way. [strapi](https://strapi.io/blog/what-is-single-source-of-truth)

